data.description: What sells a home?? The Kitchen, Primary/Master Suite and Location!! This home has it ALL and then some! This mid-century, brick ranch on a large flat lot with fenced-in backyard, will not disappoint you!  Pictures don't do this one justice!  The sellers did not leave any detail out when they added on to and renovated this home....Walk through the front door to an entry way that offers access to the formal dining area (where the sellers opened the wall) to the eat-in breakfast area, Den/Family Room and Kitchen.  The Den/Family Room offers a gas fireplace, access to the HUGE partially-covered back deck, and is open to the eat-in dining area and Kitchen. As you pass the eat-in dining area, you will see the office on your left, along with access to the 2-car garage with newer epoxy flooring.  As you enter this Chef's Dream of a Kitchen, you will see a built-in bar/glass area conveniently located next to the island where your guest can sit while you entertain!  This Amazing kitchen offers TONS of granite counter space, with plenty of cabinet space, along with Double wall ovens, gas range with vented hood, a sink in the island, and the main sink next to the dishwasher.  All stainless steel appliance (Refrigerator does convey with sale). Built in cabinet pantry next to the 19x8 pantry.  At the end of the kitchen is another small eat-in dining area, with powder room and Laundry room.  As you walk through the den, you will find the first full bathroom complete with updated cabinets, counters, fixtures, subway tile shower surround and tub.  Down the hall, there are the 2 other bedrooms, and on the left is the Master/ Primary Suite.  This Master Suite is approx 16x25 with 2 walk-in closets, and bathroom with double sink vanity, large walk in tiled shower with rain shower head and detachable, AND heated tile floors! The large deck off of the Den area is partially covered, and gives access to the fenced in back yard.  The storage shed w/ electricity will remain in AS-IS conditions.  The home does have a whole home generator, as well as dual tankless hot water heater.  Hardwoods throughout main house and master/primary suite. Tile in kitchen, powder room, laundry, pantry and 2nd bathroom.  Heated tile floor in master, and carpets in 2 additional bedrooms. NEW ROOF 9/15/2023!!!
